      "score": 4,
      "summary": "Through the door, another wave of applause rises and briefly fills the coatroom, and Tessa stands still in it the way you stand still in someone else's light, her thumb resting against the dark screen of her phone. She runs the toast back in her mind \u2014 not the cut, exactly, but the logic of it, the way a room that size needs a clean line, needs someone willing to hold the shape of the thing \u2014 and the logic feels sound enough that she almost believes it was generosity, not instinct, that made her do it. Eli's name on the screen stays unread while she finishes the thought, because once the thought is finished it will be something she can say, and something she can say is not the same as something she has to take back."
